FBIS4-55923 "dreeu101__a94013" FBIS-EEU-94-101-A Daily Report 25 May 1994 ANNEX Hungary Ministry Expresses `Concern' Over Crimea Ministry Expresses `Concern' Over Crimea AU2505111694 Budapest MTI in English 1044 GMT 25 May 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU2505111694 Budapest MTI English BFN [Text] Budapest, 25 May (MTI) -- The Hungarian Foreign Ministry on Wednesday [25 May] asked MTI to publish the following statement: "The Foreign Ministry of the Republic of Hungary expresses concern over the Crimean situation, which carries the danger of aggravating tension and thus may have an impact on the stability of not only Ukraine but even its neighbors and friends. "The Foreign Ministry welcomes and supports the efforts made by the sides concerned, primarily Ukraine, to settle the debate in a peaceful way, through negotiations. "Hungary hopes that all steps made in the next days will be based on respect for the European scale of values and international law."
